{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FGE2dniKEaoHQLrQz2gveU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a rich picture. Let me check the full npm audit for vulnerability counts and compodoc-specific issues.\n\nKey findings:\n1. `@compodoc/compodoc >=1.1.1` has 4 known vulnerable dependencies:\n   - `@angular-devkit/schematics` (vulnerable AJV)\n   - `@compodoc/live-server` (need to check this one)\n   - `uuid` (likely an older version)\n   - `vis-network` (need to check)\n\n2. AJV ReDoS via `$data` option (GHSA-2g4f-4pwh-qvx6) -- this is in compodoc's own bundled `ajv`, not the project's top-level ajv. \n\nSince this is a build-time dependency, the AJV vulnerability doesn't affect runtime. The `npx compodoc` invocation is safe in npm 7+ since it uses the local installed version first as long as the lockfile is intact. The `.catch(() => undefined)` pattern is more of a non-issue -- if documentation.json fails to load, Storybook simply won't have compodoc docs available, which isn't a real security concern. I should dig into the `@compodoc/live-server` vulnerability though, since live-server has historically had XSS issues.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2989,"cache_read_input_tokens":47565,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2989},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e63bfb4c-79d2-44ea-9cea-c81e611f37ae","uuid":"e9f415b5-db73-4bc2-852a-13477bc321cd"}
